<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wpm1665702917532.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wpm1665702917532.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wpm1665702917532.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wpm1665702917532\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Provide Uniface with the DBMS-specific information that the transaction manager (TM)\n    needs to log on to the DBMS.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__section_a3r_mhw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1196546e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Uniface indicates which transaction protocol the TM is using. The connector provides the\n        DBMS-specific information which is needed for the specified protocol. The XA protocol is\n        supported.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">For more information see the \"TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors\" topic.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__section_zdn_23x_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1196546e62\">From Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The DBMS connector must be TM-capable, (<code class=\"ph codeph\">TMCapable</code>). The current path must\n        be TM-controlled and the connector logon request has not yet been sent.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15515e1_d15516e1_d15517e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15515e1_d15516e1_d15517e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15515e1_d15516e1_d15517e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15515e1_d15516e1_d15517e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;umisc</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15515e1_d15516e1_d15517e1__entry__2\">Transaction protocol used; ‘XA’ for XA (X/Open DTP\n                Model XA).</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__section_xrq_h3x_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1196546e113\">To Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Information that is supplied to Uniface for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Global Transaction</code>\n        request, and the connector request return values.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15518e1_d15519e1_d15520e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Information supplied to Uniface protocol XA:</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15518e1_d15519e1_d15520e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15518e1_d15519e1_d15520e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15518e1_d15519e1_d15520e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;umisc</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15518e1_d15519e1_d15520e1__entry__2\">Points to the address of the DBMS’s resource manager\n                switch structure. Each DBMS provides a DBMS-specific switch table of type\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">xa_switch_t</code> . For example, send the address of\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">infx_xa_switch</code> for INFORMIX-ONLINE. <p class=\"p\">When both static and\n                  dynamic registration is possible, use static. For example, with Oracle8, static\n                    <code class=\"ph codeph\">xaosw</code> or dynamic <code class=\"ph codeph\">xaoswd</code> can be\n                used.</p></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Request Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__1\">Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__2\">Request was successful.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__1\">-1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__2\">Protocol not supported.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__1\">-3</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__2\">Exceptional error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__1\">-9 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__2\">I/O server logon error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__1\">-16</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"wpm1665702917532__table_d15521e1_d15522e1_d15523e1__entry__2\">DBMS reported network error. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrb1665702976299.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors</a><p>A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bnv1665702976230.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transactions</a><p>Most DBMSs support the concept of transactions. A transaction is a sequence of DML statements which constitute a logical unit of work.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533464\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533464\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Global Transaction ('G') Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Provide Uniface with the DBMS-specific information that the transaction manager (TM) needs to log on to the DBMS. Description Uniface indicates which transaction protocol the TM is using. The connector provides the DBMS-specific information which is needed for the specified protocol. The XA protocol is supported. For more information see the \"TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors\" topic. From Uniface The DBMS connector must be TM-capable, ( TMCapable ). The current path must be TM-controlled and the connector logon request has not yet been sent. Table 1. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->umisc Transaction protocol used; ‘XA’ for XA (X/Open DTP Model XA). To Uniface Information that is supplied to Uniface for the Global Transaction request, and the connector request return values. Table 2. Information supplied to Uniface protocol XA: Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->umisc Points to the address of the DBMS’s resource manager switch structure. Each DBMS provides a DBMS-specific switch table of type xa_switch_t . For example, send the address of infx_xa_switch for INFORMIX-ONLINE. When both static and dynamic registration is possible, use static. For example, with Oracle8, static xaosw or dynamic xaoswd can be used. Table 3. Connector Request Return Values Value Description 0 Request was successful. -1 Protocol not supported. -3 Exceptional error. -9 I/O server logon error. -16 DBMS reported network error. Related Links TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does. uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. Transactions Most DBMSs support the concept of transactions. A transaction is a sequence of DML statements which constitute a logical unit of work. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}